The following are the chief towns, with population in 1880:—Indianapolis, 75,074;
                    Evansville, 29,280; Fort Wayne, 26,880; Terre Haute, 26,040; New Albany, 16,422;
                    Lafayette, 14,860; South Bend, 13,279; Richmond, 12,473; Logansport, 11,198;
                    Jeffersonville, 10,422.
